article.headline: Utah State 89, Illinois State 84
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Mark Brown had career highs of 20 points and 13 assists to lead Utah State past Illinois State 89-84 Saturday night. Brown, who set his previous his career high of 19 against Illinois State last season, was one of five different Aggies (3-0) to score in double figures. Cardell Butler scored 14, Spencer Nelson finished with 13 points and Nate Harris and Jason Williams had 11 points apiece. The Redbirds (1-2) also had five players score in double figures and shot 62 percent (31-for-53), but that was still short of the Aggies' shooting performance. Utah State shot 67 percent (30-for-45) and outrebounded Illinois State 27-19. Neil Plank, who hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer to narrow the final margin, led the Redbirds with 21 points. Trey Guidry scored 18, Marcus Arnold finished with 14 points and Chris Burras and Vince Greene scored 12 apiece. Illinois State held a slim 31-30 lead at halftime, but only managed a single field goal in the first 5:30 of the second half. The Redbirds' slim lead was quickly turned into a deficit as Utah State built an 11-point lead in the second half, capped off by a 3-pointer by Cardell Butler. Brown's previous high for assists was 12 he had last season against Cal State Fullerton.
